<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,368,395]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Frank &amp; Sekerka, 2020" authorityName="Frank &amp; Sekerka" authorityYear="2020" box="[471,728,368,395]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dany" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[471,613,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Chrysodema</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[630,656,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[674,728,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">dany</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[737,825,369,395]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[976,1224,368,395]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneoviolacea" subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[976,995,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1019,1045,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1062,1224,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">aeneoviolacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibuyanica" subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[1281,1300,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1324,1343,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">sibuyanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as all three have dark dorsum. It can be easily distinguished by distinctly and densely micropunctate costae on elytra, thus surface appears less regular and whole dorsum appears less shiny while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[1074,1318,440,467]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneoviolacea" subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[1074,1100,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1115,1141,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1156,1318,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">aeneoviolacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has nearly polished costae without obvious micropunctures and thus dorsum is strongly shiny. 
<taxonomicName authority="Frank &amp; Sekerka, 2020" authorityName="Frank &amp; Sekerka" authorityYear="2020" box="[1089,1343,476,503]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dany" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[1089,1231,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Chrysodema</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1247,1273,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1289,1343,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">dany</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1350,1437,477,503]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has elytra usually distinctly bicoloured, costae in dark tones of blue or turquoise and intercostal depressions golden while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[220,466,548,575]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneoviolacea" subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[220,246,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[262,288,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[304,466,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">aeneoviolacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dorsum bronze-brown, pronotum often with a slight violet tinge. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibuyanica" subGenus="Chrysodema">
<emphasis box="[1244,1386,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Chrysodema</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1401,1420,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[151,272,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">sibuyanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in densely pubescent frons with long setae while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frank &amp; Sekerka" authorityYear="2020" box="[909,1047,584,611]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dany" subGenus="Chrysodema">C. (C.) dany</taxonomicName>
has it sparsely and pubescent with short setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,657,683]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after Daniel ‘Dany’ Frank, son of the senior author of this paper. The species epithet is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1237,728,755]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,899]" box="[199,1237,728,755]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,728,755]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,472,728,754]" name="Indonesia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[483,679,728,754]" country="Indonesia" name="Maluku Utara" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Maluku Province</collectingRegion>
, Haruku Island and? Seram Island (see remarks).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,765,791]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
One 
<typeStatus box="[375,471,765,791]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">paratype</typeStatus>
was supposedly collected on Seram but since it was collected by native collectors and with the same date as the rest of the type series from Haruku it might have been mislabelled. On the other hand, it is possible that 
<taxonomicName authority="Frank &amp; Sekerka, 2020" authorityName="Frank &amp; Sekerka" authorityYear="2020" box="[297,382,836,863]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysodema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dany" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[297,382,836,863]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. dany</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[388,474,837,863]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be found in southern Seram as it is only 
<quantity box="[965,1021,836,862]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="km" value="6.0">6 km</quantity>
air distance from Haruku. The occurrence on Seram should be verified with new material and until then we consider the occurrence there as doubtful.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
